summary: I tell you, every time I go to sleep some new drama develops in this fandom and I miss it completely.  Part of me is like “shit...
body:
I tell you, every time I go to sleep some new drama develops in this fandom and I miss it completely.  Part of me is like “shit I missed it”, and the other part of me is like “thank the heavens”.   I have learned over the course of 8 months, the fandom sometimes make mountains out of mole hills, and the picture of Harry and a fan is one of those times.  So what.  The girl is kissing Harry on the cheek, they are not passionately making out or anything, and even if they were, again…who cares.  I don’t get the issue here.  If you believe Harry and Louis are still together, this girl kissing Harry on the cheek means nothing.  If you believe Louis and Harry are just friends and are not in a physical relationship today, the kiss on the cheek means nothing.  If you believe Harry and Louis are enemies, the kiss on the cheek by the fan means nothing.  CONCLUSION:  No matter how you look at it, the kiss on the cheek means nothing.  I am sure she asked and Harry said yes, otherwise, the picture would never exist.

So relax (its just a picture), and enjoy the content we are getting from Harry and his friends in Tokyo. I am sure he working on something for us for the future!!!
